Peru Stocks: Cerro Verde, Credicorp, Minsur, Rio Alto Gain

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-08-11T16:55:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-11/peru-stocks-cerro-verde-credicorp-minsur-rio-alto-gain.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:40 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index rose 1.6 percent to 19,278.19. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 2.6 percent to 2,473.68.  Mining and energy companies advanced as copper and crude
oil rose after a drop in U.S. jobless claims tempered concern
the economy is slowing.  Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), Peru’s third-
largest copper producer, advanced for the second time in 10
sessions, gaining 4.1 percent to $38.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company, climbed 2.4 percent to
$2.15.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, gained 2.7 percent to 3.10 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, rose 3 percent to $1.03.
Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), the nation’s largest
petroleum refinery, advanced 2.6 percent to 80 centimos.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
holding company, rose for a second time this week after it
increased second quarter earnings 7.6 percent from a year
earlier. The Lima-based company gained 2 percent to $85.89.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
